title: 😵‍💫 "You cannot live your life looking at yourself from someone else's point of view." - Penelope Cruz
content:
Given a non-empty array containing only non-negative integers, return the list with trailing and leading zeroes removed.

Example:

> removeZeroes([0, 0, 0, 3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0])
> [3, 1, 4, 1, 5, 9]

> removeZeroes([0, 0, 0])
> []

> removeZeroes([8])
> [8]
